President Donald J. Trump and First Lady Melania Trump, in collaboration with the Department of Interior, will organize the 2020 Salute to America event on July 4th. The event, taking place on the South Lawn of the White House and Ellipse, will feature music, military demonstrations, flyovers, and a speech by the President to commemorate our nation's independence and honor our service members and veterans. The evening will conclude with a grand fireworks display over the National Mall.